  "original_title": "Sri Lanka main opposition ready to take presidency, premiership: SJB leader Sajith Premadasa",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka main opposition ready to take presidency, premiership: SJB leader Sajith Premadasa",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s main opposition the Samagi Jana Balavegaya (SJB) is ready to lead the country at the presidential and prime ministerial level and develop the economy, opposition and SJB leader Sajith Premadasa said.",
        "In a video statement released on the SJB\u2019s social media channels Monday July 11 afternoon, Premadasa said his party is ready to lead a programme aimed at bringing stability to the country.",
        "\u201cWe will appoint a government headed by a president and a prime minister. There is no other alternative. If anyone opposes this or tries to sabotage it in parliament we will see it as a treacherous act,\u201d he said.",
        "\u201cWe\u2019re ready to protect the motherland, to give leadership to the motherland, to build the economy,\u201d he added.",
        "In his statement, Premadasa also recognised the people\u2019s protests, known as the \u2018aragalaya\u2019 (struggle), that has all but seen ouster of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "\u201cVictory to the motherland, victory to the people, victory to the aragalaya,\u201d he said.",
        "\u0d86\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0da2\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0db8 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca! \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d86\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dc4\u0daf\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c\u0dd2 \u0da2\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0dc0\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca. pic.twitter.com/0bdvnviRav",
        "President Rajapaksa has yet to formally resign. According to the prime minister\u2019s office, Rajapaksa has officially communicated to Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe that he will resign on Wednesday July 13 as previously announced. However, a statement from the president\u2019s office later said that only the Speaker of Parliament can release statements from the president. (Colombo/Jul11/2022)"
      ],
